			<tr>
				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody">The fear nerf for warlocks was unfortunate.  Fear went from a relatively low cost (~85 mana) to a relatively high cost (~190, roughly equivalent to howl of terror).  
<br />

<br />
While subjectively, the increase isn't large, I only use fear as an Oh SHIT situation where I am out of life and mana (hp &lt; 10%, mana = 1%).  The low cost before meant that I could usually get off one fear and give myself half a chance of escaping even when I was almost completely out of mana.  
<br />

<br />
That option has been removed.  Now, in order to cast fear, I would have to life tap to have enough mana to cover the cost.  If I am in the situation to cast fear, I can't afford the HP cost of life tap.  Life Tap takes roughly 10% of available HP and converts this to mana.  In the situation described above, when I am already at or near 10% HP, to do so means death.  And since as a warlock, I rarely soul stone myself anymore (only when soloing), I will be doing a lot more CRs in the near future. This change has made fear a much less viable option for escape, and warlocks have very few viable escape options as it is.  
<br />

<br />
The enslave demon change is very nice.  It removed one of the deadlier counters to enslave demon.  
<br />

<br />
The Curse of Agony change is very nice indeed - will up DPS of warlocks considerably.  I routinely use +shadow damage potions and items to great effect.  I am very happy about this change.  My only concern is how it will affect agro generation.
<br />

<br />
The shadow trance change could very nice - will have to test to make sure.  Theoretically, it should now be possible to cast two shadow bolts in a row if you were casting and nightfall procs.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
