			<tr>
				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody">Just some more thoughts on the shaman reincarnate change:
<br />

<br />
Before the patch, reincarnate was almost completely useless for anything except for wipe recovery, as it was immediately followed by 10 minutes of rez sickness...  Resulting in 20% HP and MP from an already reduced mana pool (because of sickness).
<br />

<br />
Post patch, not only do I reincarnate with no horrible side effects, but the HP and MP recovered can be sizeable...  At level 44, my HP is around 2500, and my MP is sitting at a little above 5000.  If you do the math, I come out of reincarnate with 1k mana- roughly enough to heal about 3k HP, or toss around 5 totems.  2 times in the last week, I reincarnated with more mana than I died with.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
